table.name: ie_shipmentstatus
table.description: The IE series of tables is a method to store the EDI information from a Blob into a more relational format. However these may change in ver 3.0.

columns.name: I_TRANSACTION_NO
columns.description: The transaction identifier for the shipment data of the tracking event.

columns.name: SERVPROV_ALIAS_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The service provider alias qualifier identifier for the tracking event.

columns.name: SERVPROV_ALIAS_VALUE
columns.description: The service provider alias value for the qualifier defined.

columns.name: DESCRIPTION
columns.description: A description for the tracking event captured.

columns.name: STATUS_LEVEL
columns.description: A status level associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: VESSEL_CODE_QUALIFIER
columns.description: The vessel code qualifier identifier defined to itemize vessel codes.

columns.name: VESSEL_CODE
columns.description: The vessel code associated with the qualifier defined.

columns.name: COUNTRY_CODE3_GID
columns.description: The 3 digit country code that the vessel is registered in.

columns.name: VESSEL_GID
columns.description: The vessel GID.

columns.name: SHIP_OR_SAIL_DATE
columns.description: The ship sail date for the vessel used in the tracking event.

columns.name: DISCHARGE_OR_COMPLETION_DATE
columns.description: The discharge or completion date for the vessel used in the tracking event.

columns.name: FIGHT_OR_VOYAGE_NUM
columns.description: The flight number if the tracking event is for a air mode or the voyage number if for ocean mode.

columns.name: WEIGHT_VALUE
columns.description: A total weight value associated with the shipment tracking event.

columns.name: WEIGHT_VALUE_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total weight unit of measure code.

columns.name: WEIGHT_VALUE_BASE
columns.description: The total weight in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: VOLUME_VALUE
columns.description: A total volume value associated with the shipment tracking event.

columns.name: VOLUME_VALUE_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total volume unit of measure code.

columns.name: VOLUME_VALUE_BASE
columns.description: The total volume in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: OB_REFNUM_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The order base reference qualifier for the order level data of the tracking event. Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: OB_REFNUM_VALUE
columns.description: The order base reference level value for the defined qualifier.

columns.name: STATUS_CODE_GID
columns.description: The status code GID associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: TIME_ZONE_GID
columns.description: The time zone GID for the tracking event date.

columns.name: EVENTDATE
columns.description: The tracking event date.

columns.name: STATUS_REASON_CODE_GID
columns.description: The status reason code that is mapped to the tracking event.

columns.name: SS_CONTACT_FUNCTION_CODE
columns.description: The contact function code for the individual entering the tracking event.

columns.name: SS_CONTACT_NAME
columns.description: The contact name for the individual entering the tracking event.

columns.name: TRAIN_JCT_BO_CODE
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. The train junction box code for the CLM message.

columns.name: PARTITION_KEY
columns.description: The monthly range partition to manage purging status messages.

columns.name: RESPONSIBLE_PARTY_GID
columns.description: The responsible party that is defined for the type of status for the tracking event.

columns.name: RAIL_ROAD_REPORTING_SCAC
columns.description: The SCAC for the rail road service provider that is providing the shipment status message or CLM.

columns.name: IS_CAR_LOADED
columns.description: The CLM field to indicate whether the rail car is loaded or empty.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_CITY
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car destination city.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_STATE
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car destination state.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_SPLC_CODE
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car destination state.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_ETA_DATE
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the estimated time of arrival to the car destination node.

columns.name: ORIG_TRANSACTION_NO
columns.description: If this event is to adjust a previous tracking event, this field specifies the original transaction identifier.

columns.name: TEMPERATURE
columns.description: The temperature associated with the shipment tracking event.

columns.name: TEMPERATURE_BASE
columns.description: The temperature value in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TEMPERATURE_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The temperature unit of measure.

columns.name: EVENT_RECEIVED_DATE
columns.description: The time stamp for when the tracking event was received.

columns.name: DRIVER_GID
columns.description: The driver GID associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: EVENT_END_DATE
columns.description: The event end date associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: POWER_UNIT_GID
columns.description: The power unit GID associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: SHIPMENT_GID
columns.description: The shipment GID associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: DRIVER_REFNUM_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The reference number qualifier for the driver that can be used to associate to a tracking event.

columns.name: DRIVER_REFNUM_VALUE
columns.description: The driver reference number value for the reference number qualifier defined.

columns.name: PU_REFNUM_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The reference number qualifier for the power unit that can be used to associate to a tracking event.

columns.name: PU_REFNUM_VALUE
columns.description: The power unit reference number value for the reference number qualifier defined.

columns.name: RELATED_TRANSACTION_NO
columns.description: If this event is related to another tracking event this field specifies the related transaction number.

columns.name: EXTERNAL_EVENT_REFERENCE
columns.description: The reference number of the event used by the external system sending the event.

columns.name: EXTERNAL_DATA_SOURCE
columns.description: The identifying code for the external system data source.

columns.name: TIME_WORKED
columns.description: The time worked for the tracking event for recording purposes.

columns.name: TIME_WORKED_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The time worked unit of measure code.

columns.name: TIME_WORKED_BASE
columns.description: The time worked in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TIME_DRIVEN
columns.description: The time driven for the tracking event for recording purposes.

columns.name: TIME_DRIVEN_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The time driven unit of measure code.

columns.name: TIME_DRIVEN_BASE
columns.description: The time driven in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: DRIVER_CAL_EVENT_GID
columns.description: This is a GID for the driver calendar event being recorded with the tracking event, such as vacation time.

columns.name: MARKED_FOR_PURGE
columns.description: A Boolean field. When it is set to 'Y', this row and its child data will be purged.

columns.name: DOMAIN_NAME
columns.description: Database domain where this data is stored.

columns.name: INSERT_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data insert user.

columns.name: INSERT_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of data insert.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data update user.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of the most recent data update.

columns.name: ORDER_BASE_GID
columns.description: The order base identifier for the order level data of the tracking event.  Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: ORDER_RELEASE_GID
columns.description: The order release identifier for the order level data of the tracking event. Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: OR_REFNUM_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The order release reference qualifier for the order level data of the tracking event. Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: OR_REFNUM_VALUE
columns.description: The order release reference number value for the defined qualifier.

columns.name: TRACKING_NUMBER
columns.description: The specific tracking number for the shipment provided by the service provider and is matched to a reference qualifier called tracking number.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car destination location GID.

columns.name: CAR_DESTINATION_COUNTRY
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car destination country.

columns.name: ERPC
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. ERPC is a system for abbreviating rail location names.

columns.name: FILING_RESPONSE_TYPE
columns.description: The filing response type for Automated Export System (AES) via integration as tracking events.

columns.name: SHIP_GROUP_GID
columns.description: The shipment group GID associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: SHIP_GROUP_TYPE_GID
columns.description: The shipment group type (such as import, export, cargo manifest) for the shipment group associated with the tracking event.

columns.name: ORDER_RELEASE_LINE_GID
columns.description: The order release line for the order level data of the tracking event. Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: ORL_REFNUM_VALUE
columns.description: The order release line reference number value for the defined qualifier.

columns.name: OR_LINE_REFNUM_QUAL_GID
columns.description: The order release line reference qualifier for the order level data of the tracking event. Define by order base, order release, or order release line.

columns.name: INDICATOR
columns.description: A indicator that can be set to flag tracking event status.

columns.name: CAR_REPAIR_HOURS
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car repair hours.

columns.name: CAR_INTERCHANGE_ETI_DATE
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. Defines the rail car interchange date.

columns.name: NEXT_JUNCTION_SPLC
columns.description: Shipment tracking event data for rail shipments. This field specifies the interchange junction code. ETA for this junction will be Interchange ETI Date.

columns.name: LOCATION_GID
columns.description: This field describes the location at which the event occurs.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_INITIAL
columns.description: The column defines the equipment initial for the equipment for which the event occurs.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_NUMBER
columns.description: The column defines the equipment number for the equipment for which the event occurs.

columns.name: CAR_DEST_TIME_ZONE_GID
columns.description: The time zone GID for the car destination Estimated Time of Arrival date.

columns.name: CAR_INTERCHANGE_TIME_ZONE_GID
columns.description: The time zone GID for the car interchange Estimated Time of Interchange date.

columns.name: SHIPMENT_STATUS_TYPE
columns.description: Used for the ease of identification of the type of event. For example, this can be used to specify if the tracking is for matching with shipment, shipment group, order, etc.
